<TITLE> Ch'ganj teacher accused of sexual harassment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chapainawabganj, Mar 30 (bdnews24.com)  Eight female students at Chapainawabganj Government College have brought allegations of sexual harassment against a college teacher. The students submitted a letter to the deputy commissioner against Mojidul Haque, an assistant professor of the botany department. The additional deputy commissioner has been asked to investigate the matter, DC KM Azam Ali told reporters. College principal Md Sanaullah and Chapainawabganj sadar MP Abdul Odud have been sent copies of the letter, he said. The principal said the college's vice-principal had talked to the eight students. Professor Haque was not available for comment. College teachers said Haque had gone into hiding. A teacher, who did not wish to be identified, told reporters that former principal Shahjahan Karim had given Haque an oral warning in 2005 in relation to similar allegations. bd
